ack", "text": "The leaves on its head are very bitter. Eating one of these leaves is known to refresh a tired body."}, {"version": "black-2", "text": "The leaves on its head grow right back even if they fall out. These bitter leaves refresh those who eat them."}, {"version": "legends-arceus", "text": "The leaves on its head are highly valued for medicinal purposes. Dry the leaves in the sun, boil them, and then drink the bitter decoction for remarkably effective relief from fatigue."}, {"version": "moon", "text": "By pruning the leaves on its head with regularity, this Pok\u00e9mon can be grown into a fine plump shape."}, {"version": "omega-ruby", "text": "The leaves on its head are very bitter. Eating one of these leaves is known to refresh a tired body."}, {"version": "shield", "text": "The deeper the color of a Petilil\u2019s leaves, the healthier the Pok\u00e9mon is. Petilil sometimes makes its home in a well-tended field or flowerbed."}, {"version": "sun", "text": "Although the leaves on its head are bitter enough to cause dizziness, they provide relief from weariness\u2014even more so when boiled."}, {"version": "sword", "text": "Petilil appears around sources of clean water. Boiling leaves from this Pok\u00e9mon\u2019s head results in a liquid that\u2019s sometimes used as a bug repellent."}, {"version": "ultra-moon", "text": "They prefer clean water and soil. When the environment they live in turns bad, the whole bunch will up and move to a new area."}, {"version": "ultra-sun", "text": "Some say if you dry the leaves on its head, boil them down, and drink the infusion, your vigor will return, so Petilil is popular with the elderly."}, {"version": "white", "text": "Since they prefer moist, nutrient-rich soil, the areas where Petilil live are known to be good for growing plants."}, {"version": "white-2", "text": "The leaves on its head grow right back even if they fall out. These bitter leaves refresh those who eat them."}, {"version": "x", "text": "The leaves